name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Netizen contribution
"Raising a poisonous insect will eventually eat itself"
On June 20, the Taiwan Affairs Office of the State Council posted on Weibo that it would resume the entry of Taiwanese sugar apples into China, which triggered strong opposition and protests from netizens in the comment section.
The comment section was then closed, and netizens continued to repost the Weibo post in protest

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: Netizens added: Search for "Alashan Mine Disaster" on B Station, and the three most viewed videos on the homepage are all about the panda Yaya.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Netizen contribution
Under another video about "After reunification, Taiwan compatriots will truly be the masters of their own house"
Netizens all flooded the screen with reminders that "Taiwan compatriots must keep their eyes open"

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
"Nanjing Media College" has become a sensitive word?
On June 21, some netizens found that in a new game called "Peak Speed" released by NetEase, when "Nanjing Media College" was entered in the club name, it was shown that the club name contained sensitive characters.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Netizen contribution
On June 21, Sichuan University released the punishment for the female student involved in the Guangzhou subway incident: stay in school and stay in the party for observation.
This caused strong dissatisfaction among netizens in the relevant news comment area

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: Subsequently, the local police took criminal compulsory measures against the two suspects in accordance with the law on the 17th.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Netizen contribution
In recent years, with the increasingly pathological control of speech and the ever-expanding sensitive word library, content risks have already involved the level of daily government documents.
On June 21, People's Daily Online launched the "People's Review" platform for proofreading and risk control of political content. It is specifically designed to review and proofread various official documents and official releases.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Netizen contribution
"Overcoming all difficulties"
On the afternoon of June 21, the Central Academy of Fine Arts held a meeting of teachers and cadres, and the Ministry of Education announced that Lin Mao would be the president of the Central Academy of Fine Arts.
Prior to this, on June 13, the presidents and professors of the various branches of the Central Academy of Fine Arts issued a joint open letter to protest against the school's vice president Lin Mao's appointment as the new president.
